<div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
  <div class="lg:col-span-2">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">Cost Per Serving Calculator</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8 leading-relaxed">Find out how much each serving of your recipe costs, and calculate a selling price with your desired markup.</p>

    <%# Ad: leaderboard — placed below content heading per AdSense best practices %>
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "leaderboard" %></div>

    <div data-controller="cost-per-serving-calculator ad-engagement" class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:gap-8">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <label for="cost-per-serving-total-recipe-cost" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Total Recipe Cost ($)</label>
            <input id="cost-per-serving-total-recipe-cost" type="number" inputmode="decimal" data-cost-per-serving-calculator-target="totalCost" data-action="input->cost-per-serving-calculator#calculate" class="w-full" placeholder="18.00" step="0.01" min="0">
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="cost-per-serving-number-of-servings" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Number of Servings</label>
            <input id="cost-per-serving-number-of-servings" type="number" inputmode="decimal" data-cost-per-serving-calculator-target="servings" data-action="input->cost-per-serving-calculator#calculate" class="w-full" placeholder="6" step="1" min="1">
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="cost-per-serving-markup" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Markup % (optional)</label>
            <input id="cost-per-serving-markup" type="number" inputmode="decimal" data-cost-per-serving-calculator-target="markupPercent" data-action="input->cost-per-serving-calculator#calculate" class="w-full" value="0" step="5" min="0">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-indigo-900/20 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-5">Results</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Cost Per Serving</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-cost-per-serving-calculator-target="resultCostPerServing">--</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Selling Price</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" data-cost-per-serving-calculator-target="resultSellingPrice">--</span>
            </div>
            <hr class="border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Profit Per Serving</span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-cost-per-serving-calculator-target="resultProfitPerServing">--</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Total Revenue</span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-cost-per-serving-calculator-target="resultTotalRevenue">--</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Total Profit</span>
              <span class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-cost-per-serving-calculator-target="resultTotalProfit">--</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <button data-action="click->cost-per-serving-calculator#copy" class="mt-6 w-full px-4 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-indigo-600 hover:from-blue-700 hover:to-indigo-700 text-white rounded-xl shadow-sm shadow-blue-500/20 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-blue-500/25 transition-all duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 text-sm font-medium">Copy Results</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%= render "shared/calculator_rating", slug: "cost-per-serving" %>
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_results" %></div>

    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>How to Use the Cost Per Serving Calculator</h2>
      <p>
        Enter the total cost of all ingredients in your recipe and the number of servings it yields. The calculator instantly shows the cost per serving. Optionally, add a markup percentage to calculate a selling price, profit per serving, total revenue, and total profit for all servings. This makes it easy to price baked goods, meal prep, catering, or any food product for sale.
      </p>
      <p>
        To get accurate ingredient costs, add up the cost of each ingredient used in the recipe. For bulk ingredients, calculate the proportional cost. For example, if a 5-pound bag of flour costs $4 and you use 2 pounds, the flour cost for the recipe is $1.60. Being precise with ingredient costs leads to more accurate per-serving calculations.
      </p>

      <div class="my-6"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %></div>

      <h2>Pricing Food for Sale</h2>
      <p>
        Understanding cost per serving is essential for anyone selling food, whether at a farmers market, through a cottage food operation, or in a restaurant. The ingredient cost should typically be 25-35% of the selling price. This means if a serving costs $3 in ingredients, the selling price should be $8.57 to $12.00 (a markup of 186% to 300%). This margin covers labor, packaging, overhead, and profit.
      </p>

      <h3>Meal Planning on a Budget</h3>
      <p>
        Knowing the cost per serving helps you plan affordable meals. Batch cooking recipes with a low cost per serving stretches your grocery budget further. Rice and bean dishes often cost under $1 per serving, while pasta dishes average $1.50 to $2.50 per serving. Comparing cost per serving across recipes helps you choose meals that fit your budget without sacrificing nutrition or variety.
      </p>

      <h3>Scaling Recipes Up or Down</h3>
      <p>
        When scaling a recipe, the cost per serving usually stays the same, but total cost changes proportionally. Doubling a recipe doubles the total cost but keeps the per-serving cost constant. However, buying larger quantities of ingredients may lower the per-unit cost, slightly reducing the cost per serving for scaled-up recipes. Use this calculator to verify your per-serving cost after adjusting ingredient quantities and prices.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>How do I calculate cost per serving?</h3>
      <p>
        Add up all ingredient costs and divide by the number of servings. If ingredients cost $18 and the recipe makes 6 servings, each serving costs $3.00.
      </p>

      <h3>What is a good markup for selling homemade food?</h3>
      <p>
        A standard markup is 200-300%. A $3 dish would sell for $9-12. Higher-end items can command 400% or more. Consider your market, competition, and overhead costs.
      </p>

      <h3>How do I account for ingredient waste?</h3>
      <p>
        Add 10-15% to your total ingredient cost for waste and spoilage. For produce-heavy recipes, add 15-20%. This gives a more realistic cost per serving.
      </p>

      <h3>Should I include labor cost in my cost per serving?</h3>
      <p>
        For personal cooking, no. For a food business, multiply ingredient cost by 3-4x to cover labor, packaging, utilities, and profit.
      </p>

      <h3>How can I reduce the cost per serving?</h3>
      <p>
        Buy ingredients in bulk, use seasonal produce, substitute expensive ingredients, cook in larger batches, and reduce waste through proper meal planning and storage.
      </p>

